It could be very handful to have this method to use with TextureButtons nodes for theming GUI with special fx and such.

Some example code would look this way:

``` javascript

var face_request
var face_requestd

func _process(delta):
   var face_happy = get_node("TextureButton_happy").is_hovered()
   var face_normal = get_node("TextureButton_normal").is_hovered()
   var face_sad = get_node("TextureButton_sad").is_hovered()
   if face_happy:
      face_request = "happy"
   if face_normal:
      face_request = "normal"
   if face_sad:
      face_request = "sad"
   if face_request != face_requested:
      get_node("SpriteFace").set_texture(face_request)
      face_requested = face_request

```
